						               													<description>Hodge Podge is played on a 9x9 square board.Each player starts with 18 stones(17 Soldiers and 1 King)9 on each of the two back ranks.&amp;#10;On each turn each player must move one stone:&amp;#10;1.Soldiers and Kings slide an orthogonal line of empty cells.&amp;#10;2.A stone may jump over an orthogonal adjacent stone(of either color)landing on the immediate empty cell.This is not a capture.&amp;#10;3.A stone may capture stones by custodian capture,i.e.sandwiching the opponent&amp;acute;s stones between itself and a friend over an orthogonal line.A capture along an edge may wrap around the corner.&amp;#10;Wins the player that satisfies one of the following conditions:&amp;#10;1.Capture the opponent King&amp;#10;2.Move your King into the last row&amp;#10;3.Make a 5 in-a-row including your King and not using stones over the first two rows.&amp;#10;4.Reduce the opponent&amp;acute;s army to less than 4 soldiers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
